# 📊 Automated Visual Data Report

### AI-Assisted Data Cleaning & Trend Analysis for Regional Development

**Dataset Focus:** Mindanao Municipal Waste Generation Trends (Mock CSV Analysis)

**Role:** Data Analyst – Regional Development Council / Environmental Monitoring Coalition
**Audience:** Regional Policymakers and LGU Department Heads

---

## 📌 Project Objective

This project demonstrates how an AI-supported data workflow can rapidly transform a disorganized regional dataset into readable visual intelligence for emergency policy planning.

The objective was to clean structural inconsistencies, isolate meaningful indicators, and produce high-contrast visual outputs appropriate for government decision-making.

---

# 1. Data Cleaning Protocol Log

### Raw Dataset Conditions

The uploaded CSV simulation contained:

* Missing entries across municipal reporting periods
* Mixed measurement units (tons, kilograms)
* Duplicate municipality labels
* Inconsistent date formatting
* Non-standard numeric separators
* Empty category cells

---

### AI Cleaning Instructions

```text id="4x9m2o"
Scan the dataset.

Standardize all measurement units into Metric Tons (MT).

Identify missing values and apply median replacement by municipality category.

Remove duplicate observations.

Normalize date formatting to YYYY.

Trim invalid spaces and harmonize municipality naming.

Export cleaned structure for analysis.
```

---

### Structural Adjustments Applied

| Issue             | Cleaning Action            | Result                                |
| :---------------- | :------------------------- | :------------------------------------ |
| Missing Values    | Median imputation          | Completed missing annual observations |
| Mixed Units       | Converted to Metric Tons   | Unified reporting scale               |
| Duplicate Records | Removed duplicates         | Reduced redundancy                    |
| Formatting Errors | Standardized labels        | Improved grouping                     |
| Invalid Dates     | Converted to annual format | Enabled trend analysis                |

### Cleaning Outcome

* Raw records: **145**
* Valid records after cleaning: **132**
* Fields normalized: **6**
* Data retention rate: **91%**

